FIG. 6.
In the b = 0 images (i.e., the non-DWIs), unreliable regions in terms of signal variability (most likely due to pulsation artifacts) can be visualized readily by taking the standard deviation across the b = 0 images (Sb = 0). For the example shown here, six b = 0 images were acquired. Notice the high variability near the medial parts of the brainstem,
cerebellum, and the lateral ventricles.

