FIG. 16. Whole-brain nontensor probabilistic tractography results displayed as a coronal 2-mm-thick section. Each track is colored according to its direction of travel (red: left–right; green: anterior–posterior; blue: inferior–superior). 100,000 tracks were produced by seeding at random throughout the brain, with a probabilistic streamlines algorithm using fiber orientation distributions estimated using constrained spherical deconvolution (99), based on the same data as shown in Fig. 8. Note in particular the extensive regions of crossing fibers in the pons and periventricular areas.

